  <work>
    <work-number>(also known as Herod Why Dreadest thou a Foe? or How Vain the Cruel Herod's Fear or
When Christ's Appearing Was Made Known or Why Herod Unrelenting Foe or
Why Impious Herod, Shouldst Thou Fear)</work-number>
    <work-title>The Star Proclaims the King is Here</work-title>
  </work>
  <identification>
    <creator type="composer">Words: Coelius Sedulius, c. 450. German version by M. Luther, 1543.  English translation by John Mason Neale, 1852.
Music: 'Wo Gott Zum Haus' from Klug's Geistliche Lieder, Wittenberg, 1533.
Setting: "Kern des Deutschen Kirchengesangs", 1855, alt.
copyright: public domain.  This score is a part of the Open Hymnal Project, 2009 Revision.</creator>
